### Description

Following transform usecase does not work currently

```
function newTransform() {
  return (value: string | number): string => {
      return value.toString()
  }
}

@Input({trasnform: newTrasnform()}) someInput //this does not work
```

## Why this usecase should be supported

Allowing above kind of way of adding trasnform function will make this feature very powerful. We can leverage closure to have internal variable. Example. below transform function can be used to create observable input

```
function newTransform() {
  const subject = new ReplaySubject()
  return (value: string): Observable<string> => {
      subject.next(value)
      return subject
  }
}

@Input({trasnform: newTrasnform()}) someObservableInput //this does not work
```

Without this support input transform will be used for a very limited usecase. As more developers start using input transform they might expect these usecases to work.

### Proposed solution

Support transform function with complex typing

### Alternatives considered

Maybe allow only few preset transform function like coerceToBoolean. So that developer know inout transform has only limited application and should not experimented with to support more complex usecase

